commit.message:
Merge pull request #8 from pimlu/master

update to v1.1

add proper lighting

game now lights up when the ball rolls as if you pressed a button
add proper lighting

actually fix movement, fix select speedbug

funnily enough, pressing the select button again and again would start more gameloops.  you could play maze at hyperspeed.  now movement actually prioritizes the direction you're leaning, but not to the exclusion of other directions.  it used to be that if there was no wall to the right or north of you and you were leaning northnorthwest, it would still go right instead.  after the first attempted fix, it would go north in that situation, but if there was a wall to the north, it actually would refuse to go west, which is even worse.  now this fixes everything (as far as I know)
actually fix movement, fix select speedbug

fix diagonal tilt bug and subtle frame stutter

previously, the game would prioritize x movement over y movement, even if you were tilted in the y direction more.  this is fixed.

also, the app no longer waits a frame each time it moves.  before this was fixed, this would mean that, assuming the corridorWidth was 8, it would roll down a long hallway spending 9 frames per unit movement, moving 1 px 8 frames of the time, but halting and moving 0px for a single frame.

remove light_enable

after our experiences with the battery, probably a bad idea

fix redundant loop in maze.c

the original function needed a loop, but it turned out to be all that was necessary because of the way it was written.  I was tired at the time and quit looking at it the moment it worked. lol
